      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Easter 1896 ¶ Your genial and extensive letter ¶  has been most cheering to me, dear Sir Joseph, and it most gratifying, that you – altho’ now nearly an Octogenarian – you ¶  are in so youthful a vigo...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">96.04.05</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Joseph Hooker</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Letters to Joseph Hooker, vol. 16, ff. 26-27.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Easter 1896<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Easter Day was 5 April 1896.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Your genial and extensive letter<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>J. Hooker to M, 2 March 1896.</p>
               </note> has been most cheering to me, dear Sir Joseph, and it most gratifying, that you – altho’ now nearly an Octogenarian – you<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>you <seg style="font-style: italic; ">repeated.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> are in so youthful a vigor and spirit yet able to push on such most difficult work as the agrostographic.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Hooker was writing much of the section on grasses for Volume 7 of J. Hooker (1872–97), a task he found very difficult.</p>
               </note> May you long be spared with your unrivalled phytographic experience to carry on your researches and thus to furnish also yet a supplemental volume for the Flora of India.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Of those, whose researches far back into the first half of the Century in phytography and who have largely borne the burden, are left besides yourself only Agardh, Carl Muell[.]<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Obscured by the binding strip, as in all cases below except</seg> Du[char]tre,<seg style="font-style: italic; "> which is a doubtful reading.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> and myself are left<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>are left <seg style="font-style: italic; ">repeated</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> after recently Alphonse DC,<note xml:id="ftn7" type="footnote" n="7">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>De Candolle.</p>
               </note> Du[char]tre, Baillon, Babington[,] Jean Mueller, Willkomm have passed away; all others now yet prominently working on our principle lines among the elder did arise only in the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">second half of the century</hi>
               </seg>. If I can claim to be among the few Nestor[s,] it is on the ground, that I commenced in 1839 my observations on the plants of the Dutchy<note xml:id="ftn8" type="footnote" n="8">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Duchy?</p>
               </note> of Schleswig, resulting in a complete elaboration of the Flora of its south-western region. My “Breviarium” was <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">finished 1845</hi>
               </seg>, but only published some years afterwards,<note xml:id="ftn9" type="footnote" n="9">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Published in two parts: B53.08.01, B53.08.02.</p>
               </note> as I left the University in 1847, to proceed to the dry warm Australia, being well aware that I should fall otherwise a victim to phthisis in the winter of 1847-1848. Thus then I shall celebrate my 50 years Doctor jubilee next year, if merciful providence will spare my life so long.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The long essay on the plants of the Elder-Expedition is at last nearly ready as I could only devote Sundays and Holidays on it, far more urgent work for the practical welfare of the colony pressing on me during Office-days. The share, which Prof Tate had in this joint treatise of course was much lighter than mine.<note xml:id="ftn10" type="footnote" n="10">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>B96.14.02.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Let me remain, dear Sir Joseph, </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">When this letter will arrive, your will approach an other birthdays festivity of yours, for which, I offer my best felicitation. Your natal day is precisely the same as mine, 30 June, but yours is 7 years more.<note xml:id="ftn11" type="footnote" n="11">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>but yours … more <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>written in left margin of back of f. 27.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have the third Census of Australian Plants ready for the press. It contains about 200 additional, many hundred more geographic entries and copious emendations for authorities. The work serves also as an index to the Flor. Austral. and Fragmenta.<note xml:id="ftn12" type="footnote" n="12">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">I have the third ... Fragmenta<seg style="font-style: italic; "> is written in the margins on the back f. 26 and the front of f. 27.</seg>
                  </p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     </seg>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The third edition of M’s <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Census</seg> was not published.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
         </div>
      </body>
